				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E=0$$\end{document}E=0 calculated using the continuum model described in Refs. 8,9. Only the first two moiré valence bands of the K-valley states are illustrated. They carry Chern number C = +1. The corresponding moiré bands of the K’-valley states are a time-reversal copy and carry Chern number C = −1. The DOS shows a vHS that is aligned with the saddle point in the first moiré band, and a second vHS, with the saddle point in the second moiré band. The Fermi level crosses the first vHS at hole filling \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
